review.description: The cassolet was a complete ripoff. There was not one morsel of duck or sausage or bacon for that matter. It was a large crock of very tasty white beans in sauce but for 19 dollars a bite of duck was expected. I wanted to like this homey restaurant and I enjoyed the cheese and meat starter but really, it was very disappointing.
review.author: Judith D.

review.description: Excellent French bistro, fresh food, great atmosphere. Love the Brandade.
review.author: Olivier B.

review.description: Great intimate spot. Everything is spot on here, food, wine, music and ambiance. Genuinely feels like being in a cafe in France.
review.author: Daniel D.

review.description: This place looked cute, but I was stunned to see that they billed me 7 dollars for a small glass of orange juice.   My latte was poorly made, and also the smallest I've ever seen.   26 bucks for a small glass of juice, a poorly made latte and some eggs.   No thanks.
review.author: Jennifer F.

review.description: very nice and cozy place, had dinner with my friend there. the food was very good, but service........ i wish it could be better
review.author: Janna Y.
